bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
    UFD = a value determined by applying, in accordance with the MIPM, the
update factor for the first year of designation to the value of A - UF - I +
  D;

    ID = a value determined by applying, in accordance with the MIPM, the
interest factor for the first year of designation to the value of
  A - UF - I + D + UFD;

bcl:definition.bcl:text:
final determination means any change in assessment that is
finally determined under the Assessment Act by a supplementary
assessment roll or on further appeal;

MIPM means the Major Industrial Properties Manual established
or adopted under section
  20 (5) of the Assessment Act;
